"“The book lacks focus and precision, often reducing some of the most significant moments of her life to mere footnotes…If there’s a storytelling cliché available, Dinelaris made sure to use it in the book...'On Your Feet!' has a structure that aimed for fractured cinematic-ness, but ends up merely just being confused...Fortunately the show has the music to fall onto, and with songs like 'Mi Tierra' and 'Reach' audience members should have a fine time regardless."
